Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Dirk Seidensticker/Clemens Schmid

  1. Februar 2016

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

ggplot2 und die Daten laden:

library(ggplot2)
df <- read.csv("downloads/r-tut/data/AtlantPottery.csv", sep = '\t')

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Einfacher Plot

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH)) + 
  geom_point()

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Gleichmige X- und Y-Achse

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_equal()

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Symbolgre manuell einstellen

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH)) + 
  geom_point(size = 3) + 
  coord_equal()

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Symbolgre abhngig von Variable

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH, size = wall)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_equal()

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Grenzen fr Symbolgre

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH, size = wall)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_equal() + 
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(2,15))

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Fllfarbe

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH, size = wall, color = site)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  coord_equal() + 
  scale_size_continuous(range = c(2,15))

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Symboltypen

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH, color = site, shape = vesselShape)) + 
  geom_point(size = 4) + 
  coord_equal()

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

manuelle Angabe der Symbole

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH, color = site, shape = vesselShape)) + 
  geom_point(size = 4) + 
  coord_equal() + 
  scale_shape_manual(values = 1:(1+length(unique(df$vesselShape))))

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Facettierung der Daten

ggplot(df, aes(x = maxD, y = muendungsH, color = site, shape = vesselShape)) + 
  geom_point(size = 4) + 
  coord_equal() + 
  scale_shape_manual(values = 1:(1+length(unique(df$vesselShape)))) + 
  facet_wrap(~ feature_simple)

Anwendung 2: Scatterplot

Position der Legende & fertiger Plot

ggplot(df, aes(
  x = maxD, 
  y = muendungsH, 
  color = site, 
  shape = vesselShape)
  ) + 
  geom_point(size = 4) + 
  coord_equal() + 
  scale_shape_manual(values = 1:(1+length(unique(df$vesselShape)))) + 
  facet_wrap(~ feature_simple) + 
  theme(legend.direction ="horizontal",legend.position = "bottom")
